			<CASNumber>124-38-9; 74-82-8; 10024-97-2</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Greenhouse gases, such as carbon dioxide (CO2), methane (CH4), and nitrous oxide (N2O), are atmospheric gases that trap heat, leading to the greenhouse effect and warming the Earth's surface. They are significant in the study of climate change, as they absorb radiation emitted by the planet. Human activities have been the main driver of climate change since the mid-20th century, largely due to emissions of these gases. Industries like electricity generation, aluminum production, and cement production are among the sources of greenhouse gas emissions.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">温室气体，如二氧化碳（CO2）、甲烷（CH4）和氧化亚氮（N2O），是一种能够捕获热量、导致温室效应和地球表面变暖的大气气体。它们吸收地球发出的辐射，对研究气候变化意义重大。自 20 世纪中期以来，人类活动一直是气候变化的主要驱动力，这主要是由于这些气体的排放造成的。发电、铝生产和水泥生产等行业都是温室气体的排放源。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>CO2; CH4; N2O</sumFormula>
